            <div corresp="#c1607f2">
                <head>Trebizond, Turkey</head>
                <p>Consul Veizer was instructed by the Am. Embassy at Constantinople Apr. 2, 1916 to
                    return to Constantinople. He left Trebizond May 10, and proceeded to
                    Constantinople via Batoum, Bakow, Moscow, Petrograd and Sweden arriving there
                    June 5, 1916.</p>
                <p>Consul Class 8 took over the office from Vice Con Montesanto July 11, 1916;
                    turned over office to Vice Consul Montesanto reported Jan. 15, 1918, this office
                    January 15, 1918.</p>
                <p>Vice Consul Montesanto October 1, 1917 and left for Tiflis; Vice Consul Jenkins
                    had left for Tiflis Jan. 14, 1918. Montesanto took over this office January 15,
                    1918.</p>
                <p>Promoted Consul, Class 6 Sep. 5, 1919; did not open Consulate. Returned to
                    Constantinople.</p>
                <p>Consul, Cl 8, detailed, temporarily to Trebizond July 23, 1919 &amp; reopen
                    Consulate; appt'd Consul Class 6 Sep. 5, 1919; did not open Consulate. Returned
                    to Constantinople.</p>
